  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Ishinomaki Social Farm for Elderly Care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Elderly people in the disaster area make friends and have fun by participating in agriculture activities. After having lost their houses and family it is difficult to reestablish their lives. Many of them live in temporary housing and live solitary lives. We set up social farms that enable them to interact with others and find a purpose to get excited about another day. Together with trained psychologists and volunteers we provide them with daily activities that get them out of the house.</narrative>
  </description>
